-- Australia to Propose Tougher Penalties for Aviation Crimes, Minister Says
-- Jacob Greber
-- 2010-06-13T22:47:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-13/australia-to-propose-tougher-penalties-for-aviation-crimes-minister-says.html

          
          
             Australia proposes to introduce
tougher penalties for aviation crimes such as bomb hoaxes and
endangering an aircraft in flight, Home Affairs Minister Brendan
O’Connor said today in a statement. The maximum penalty for hoax
offences will increase to 10 years prison from 2 years, O’Connor
said in the statement.  
